  "text": "Five samples (200 mL) were taken from five evenly distributed points within each bioreactor volume. The procedures for sampling and pretreatment for DNA extraction followed those described by Ni et al. [CITATION_1] . Biomass was separated from the collected wastewater by centrifugation at 3500 rpm for 10 minutes at room temperature in a Kokusan H-103N series apparatus (Kokusan Enshinki Co., Ltd., Tokyo, Japan). Pelleted biomass was stored at −20 ∘ C before DNA extraction.",
